FBIS4-63348 "drsov099_a_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 23 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Minister Views Ukrainian `Provocation' in Crimea Minister Views Ukrainian `Provocation' in Crimea LD2305080994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0435 GMT 23 May 94 LD2305080994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Mikhail Shevtsov and Andrey Palariya] [Text] Moscow, 23 May -- This morning Internal Affairs Minister Valeriy Kuzentsov announced that the situation in Crimea is being monitored. At the same time, he said, yesterday the Ukrainian minister of internal affairs sent all town and rayon departments telegrams with orders to obey instructions from Kiev only. Valeriy Kuznetsov assessed this step by the Ukrainian leadership as a provocation aimed at destabilizing the situation on the peninsula. The duty officer of the Black Sea Fleet staff told TASS that, following the completion of routine exercise, all units and subunits of the fleet are in their permanent places of deployment. They are not carrying out any maneuvers at present.
